1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:04,800
After Venezuela's earthquakes, finding
emergency help shouldn't be hard.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:08,200
It's a Telegram bot for
the earthquake response.

3
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:13,900
Ask in plain Spanish, and get clear answers
on shelters, water, and missing people.

4
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:19,000
Ask how many people are reported missing —
it answers from live data.

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:23,200
Search for someone by name —
real records, in seconds.

6
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:26,600
Ask for the latest news — always current.

7
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:30,900
No app. No sign-up. Just help,
where people already are.

8
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:34,600
And behind it: Gecko.

9
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:39,400
Point it at any API's spec, and in seconds
it's agent-usable.

10
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:43,700
The agent calls it correctly, first try —
zero integration code.
